The Telegraph - Calcutta : Bengal
 Friday, May 21, 2004 				 Purulia 47.3, Bankura 44
 OUR BUREAU																								Purulia, May 20: The district town recorded 47.3 degree Celsius this afternoon as a heat wave continued its sweep.																								The maximum temperature here had been hovering between 45 and 46 degrees for the past four days. Three people have died of heat-induced fever and diarrhoea. Many more are in hospital.																								Neighbouring Bankura is sweating as well. It was 44 degrees in the town this afternoon. Water scarcity made it worse. The groundwater level in Purulia is also fast depleting.																								The heat has impaired the cooling system at the Purulia Sadar Hospital morgue, the only one in the district. 																								A woman in Bagnan, Howrah, collapsed while cooking lunch at home. Doctors said she died of the heat.
